				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">What do you think you're doing while twisting, RP wise?<a name="54888"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 3 04 8:13 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have always sort of justified twisting as it being 1 song with different sounds per different twists.  The 'songs' are really just elements to be played in the song.  For example, a fast tempo is speeding you up (haste), while an age-old rhyme might make you feel safer (PoV), calm instruments are regenerating your health (regen and mana song), etc.
<br />

<br />
While it's probably VERY difficult to actually make songs that incorporate all of this, keep in mind that they're incredibly skilled musicians that have been working with music every day for years and years and years.
<br />

<br />
What I have trouble with, though, is the single target detrimental songs.  How on earth does a song burn and freeze and poison and disease oine thing fairly far away?  Especially if it's an animal?  Are they really doing some sort of magical chant that works like magic or just so amazingly talented that no person in the 'real world' has managed to find a way to come close to matching their talents?  
<br />

<br />
Anyways, did you ever justify it or just said you're singing multiple songs?  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
