			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What do you think you're doing while twisting, RP wise?<a name="54893"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 3 04 9:27 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>--Comon now bardtail the poster said it was in a RP sense, no need to get all cynical.
<br />

<br />
I never really tried to justify what it is I'm doing. I would say that through the magic of the songs we are able to perform multiple symphonies that harmonize with one another.
<br />

<br />
However, playing the same symphony on top of itself would not sound very good thus, you cannot sing certain songs that are related in this way, or their affects may not work well together.
<br />

<br />
Furthermore, the act of twisting is not so much ending one song and starting another, thats just what we tell the common-folk. In fact, we are extending our voice beyond singing one note at any given time.
<br />

<br />
Surprisingly, all races of Norrath have some amount of affinity for music, but they are limited in scope because they lack the magical talents that true bards possess. These talents allow the true bard the versitility to sing with a hundred voices.
<br />

<br />
Ogres, though they would never know it, are quite attuned to rythm. Their war drums and thunderous marches shatter the moral of their enemies while rallying their own troops' bloodlust.
<br />

<br />
Similarly, the Guktan have always used music in their daily lives. In the ages past, soft harmonies of sorrow played out nightly from deep within the worn halls of Guk. Visitors, horrified by the endless croaking of a thousand guktan voices, would years after recall the nightmares of their haunting hymn.
<br />

<br />
It is not really known how we, as bards, are able to multiply are voice. Truth be told, it probably wouldn't be wise to give away our secrets. Should the enemies of Norrath learn our technique, an army of unstoppable evil would emerge and we shall all be doomed. We are the last guardians of a sacred magic, one which may prove to be the ultimate salvation of Norrath.
<br />

<br />
Sing true, and may your voice be guided by the light.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
