			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What do you think you're doing while twisting, RP wise?<a name="54996"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 3 04 6:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This is my take on the whole &quot;twisting&quot; RP aspect..... take in mind, I'm a classically trained musician, so it was 'fate' for me to play a bard....
<br />

<br />

<br />
Twisting was the act of 2, 3 or 4 Troubadour's around the 12th century traveling from ministry to ministry, in search of knowledge (mostly religeous, but sometimes not). Anyway, during these travels, they would basically keep the same pace (walking tempo) by singing songs.  Occaisionally it was the same song, but in most instances, they would sing different songs, creating a harmony of different songs, therefor, creating a twisting sensation.... or a Motet.  Take in point, the song <i>O mitissima / Virgo / Haec dies</i>.  Anyway, this was back in times of bardic troupe's, and traveling minstrels, so I like to think that in this occaision, Verant was pretty well on their lore, and history, as it were....
<br />

<br />

<br />
As  JyveAFK was stating on the &quot;physics&quot; of things, I have a feeling he's on the right path.... remember Dune.....
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
of course, these are only my opinions, and what my feeble little mind has been able to absorb when it came to Music History (yes, I did have to pull out some of my old notes to get the songs right, and the 'nomenclature').
<br />

<br />

<br />
Thanks for reading,
<br />

<br />
Tacklar
<br />
52 Half-Elf Minstrel
<br />
&lt;League of Chaos&gt;
<br />
Tunare
