				<td colspan="2"><span>I've always imagined that twisting is not so much starting one song and stopping another, but melding 3 or 4 songs together in harmony, IRL it would take an incredible musician i think to mix multiple songs together on the fly (on an instrument such as guitar or piano perhaps?) but from what i understand you could do it if they were in the same key?
<br />

<br />
As for the actual specifics on how a chant works, the War of Shadow and Light by Janny Wurts has a lead character (who goes by the name of Arithon strangely enough) who can effect strange powers by somehow hitting perfectly pure notes that resonate with the molecules of matter around him, or something like that.  sounds plausible enough for a fantasy description to me.
