				<td colspan="2"><span>Best I have ever heard was a violinist who did some free-form improvisations and he was using the tempo from one melody together with the main chorus of another by plucking strings with one hand, clamping the violin with his chin and playing it traditionally at the same time.
<br />

<br />
Ok, ok, when he lost the tempo it went from bizar but nice to being so bad a cat would have lobbed a shoe at him.
<br />

<br />
As for magic, well, you could say our singing and instrumentals are the verbatim parts of the spells we cast and instead of components for casting we replace those with somatic parts.</span></td>
