				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What do you think you're doing while twisting, RP wise?<a name="55148"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 4 04 3:52 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm not very musical IRL so I didn't know the term Stretto Fugue, but that sounds much like how I envisioned it.
<br />

<br />
I always thought of the different spells we got as knowledge of different ways of playing, and when we 'twisted' we were combining those knowledges into one song.  The song I'm playing is one, everchanging tune, with different aspects to it.  A strong rythem to boost speed and spirits, a loud wailing scream to peirce the ears of my victim, slow lullabyes to soothe or hypnotize my audience etc, all being used together in a forever-improvising jam.  Kinda like a dead show except played by a ambidexterous schizophrenic <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
